1
00:00:19,233 --> 00:00:20,400
I know where she is.

2
00:00:20,467 --> 00:00:21,567
I'll just bring her back to you.

3
00:00:21,633 --> 00:00:22,600
I want

4
00:00:22,667 --> 00:00:23,567
- Patricio...
- to fetch my daughter.

5
00:00:23,633 --> 00:00:25,467
Patricio,
just leave it to Mikoy.

6
00:00:25,533 --> 00:00:26,533
If she sees you,

7
00:00:26,600 --> 00:00:28,300
the more Celeste
might not come along.

8
00:00:28,367 --> 00:00:31,333
But, Mikoy, you should come back
with my daughter.

9
00:00:31,400 --> 00:00:32,267
Promise that.

10
00:00:33,700 --> 00:00:35,100
Ouch!

11
00:00:35,167 --> 00:00:36,133
Celeste.

12
00:00:36,967 --> 00:00:38,100
Mikoy?

13
00:00:38,167 --> 00:00:40,500
Maybe you're just making
our project an alibi.

14
00:00:40,567 --> 00:00:41,400
You choose.

15
00:00:41,467 --> 00:00:44,233
Your jealousy or we fail?

16
00:00:44,300 --> 00:00:46,533
Okay, I'll agree
but on one condition.

17
00:00:46,600 --> 00:00:48,233
You need to be always with me.

18
00:00:48,300 --> 00:00:50,433
Just don't be a jerk.

19
00:00:50,500 --> 00:00:52,133
You're just mine, Tiffany.

20
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:54,967
You shouldn't judge
your father that much.

21
00:00:55,033 --> 00:00:56,267
You should talk.

22
00:00:56,333 --> 00:00:58,400
You should also talk
to your Auntie Adora.

23
00:00:58,467 --> 00:00:59,767
Don't be too hard.

24
00:00:59,833 --> 00:01:01,400
Come on, let's go home.

25
00:01:01,467 --> 00:01:03,000
I will not go home.
I'll stay here.

26
00:01:03,067 --> 00:01:05,767
Okay, if you want
to contemplate, go ahead...

27
00:01:05,833 --> 00:01:07,500
but I will not leave you.
I'll stay here.

28
00:01:07,600 --> 00:01:08,667
I'm not here.

29
00:01:10,400 --> 00:01:11,300
Yes, Vivian?

30
00:01:11,367 --> 00:01:14,200
I'll send you some
documents tonight.

31
00:01:14,267 --> 00:01:16,767
Read them and let me know
what you think.

32
00:01:16,833 --> 00:01:18,367
Sir, Celeste, and I
are together now.

33
00:01:18,433 --> 00:01:19,267
Don't worry anymore.

34
00:01:19,333 --> 00:01:20,833
Why you didn't come back?

35
00:01:20,900 --> 00:01:23,733
She twisted her ankle
but I applied first aid already.

36
00:01:23,800 --> 00:01:26,667
Let's just leave Celeste alone
and let her think things over.

37
00:01:26,733 --> 00:01:28,067
I beg you.

38
00:01:28,133 --> 00:01:29,100
Take care of my daughter.

39
00:01:29,167 --> 00:01:30,000
Don't worry,

40
00:01:30,067 --> 00:01:31,867
once she's okay tomorrow,

41
00:01:31,933 --> 00:01:33,600
we'll go home right away.

42
00:01:33,667 --> 00:01:34,900
You were right.
If you didn't come,

43
00:01:34,967 --> 00:01:36,833
maybe...

44
00:01:36,900 --> 00:01:38,200
something happened to me.

45
00:01:42,233 --> 00:01:45,100
And I'm sorry if...

46
00:01:45,167 --> 00:01:46,967
sometimes I'm a troublemaker.

47
00:01:50,033 --> 00:01:51,200
Sometimes?

48
00:01:52,300 --> 00:01:53,667
It seems always.

49
00:01:56,667 --> 00:01:57,467
Okay,
I'm always a trouble maker.

50
00:01:57,533 --> 00:01:58,667
Let's change it.

51
00:02:00,600 --> 00:02:01,567
I'm principled.

52
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:06,500
Spoiled brat.

53
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:12,967
I thought you knew me
but it seems you don't.

54
00:02:14,500 --> 00:02:16,700
You really changed a lot,
Celeste.

55
00:02:19,133 --> 00:02:23,100
Manila had taught you a lot

56
00:02:23,167 --> 00:02:24,600
and being a troublemaker
is one of them.

57
00:02:26,667 --> 00:02:28,867
It's called survival instinct.

58
00:02:30,067 --> 00:02:32,267
Sometimes you have to be strong.

59
00:02:33,867 --> 00:02:35,300
You have to be fierce...

60
00:02:36,400 --> 00:02:40,133
because you have to protect
yourself.

61
00:02:41,267 --> 00:02:42,700
I was alone then.

62
00:02:44,433 --> 00:02:45,733
My father...

63
00:02:47,600 --> 00:02:48,800
has another family.

64
00:02:48,867 --> 00:02:51,633
I have no one to rely on
but myself.

65
00:02:52,833 --> 00:02:54,833
And life was never easy for me.

66
00:02:56,667 --> 00:02:58,867
I've been through a lot.

67
00:02:58,933 --> 00:02:59,967
It's too much.

68
00:03:01,633 --> 00:03:03,100
I suffered a lot.

69
00:03:03,867 --> 00:03:07,033
I worked hard a lot to get
to where I am now...

70
00:03:09,633 --> 00:03:10,933
but I was broken.

71
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:19,067
Good thing, Tonito came...

72
00:03:19,133 --> 00:03:20,667
he mended me

73
00:03:20,767 --> 00:03:22,267
and made me whole again.

74
00:03:24,500 --> 00:03:25,600
Is that why you don't want
to look back

75
00:03:25,667 --> 00:03:26,900
to where you came from?

76
00:03:29,567 --> 00:03:33,367
Maybe anyone who has a bad past
wouldn't want to look back.

77
00:03:36,733 --> 00:03:37,967
It can't be that bad.

78
00:03:42,300 --> 00:03:44,967
You know, no matter how bad
you've gone through...

79
00:03:46,733 --> 00:03:52,300
there's always a good memory
that will be left.

80
00:03:55,433 --> 00:03:59,200
Like now, it's dark...

81
00:03:59,267 --> 00:04:00,133
but there's a bonfire

82
00:04:00,200 --> 00:04:02,300
so, somehow there's light,
right?

83
00:04:03,767 --> 00:04:07,600
So, no matter how dark it
was for you then

84
00:04:07,667 --> 00:04:13,767
maybe there's a little fire that
gave light, right?

85
00:04:13,833 --> 00:04:15,333
You just don't want to see that.

86
00:04:16,467 --> 00:04:19,000
Either you're ignoring,
you're playing blind,

87
00:04:19,067 --> 00:04:21,133
- or...
 - Playing dumb?

88
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:25,567
You said that again not me.

89
00:04:28,033 --> 00:04:29,467
Maybe not.

90
00:04:29,533 --> 00:04:31,900
I don't want to look back
because I'm not going that way.

91
00:04:34,300 --> 00:04:36,333
I was really traumatized.

92
00:04:38,733 --> 00:04:41,633
Father hurt me and up to now,
he's still hurting me.

93
00:04:46,133 --> 00:04:48,133
I understand what you feel.

94
00:04:49,533 --> 00:04:51,300
I was also hurt before.

95
00:04:57,200 --> 00:04:58,467
We're the same.

96
00:04:59,733 --> 00:05:01,667
Yes...

97
00:05:01,767 --> 00:05:03,167
but the difference
between us is,

98
00:05:03,233 --> 00:05:05,333
I'm willing to give
a second chance

99
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:07,867
to the person who hurt me.

100
00:05:09,367 --> 00:05:11,200
A second chance to make up
for it.

101
00:05:13,733 --> 00:05:14,667
You should too.

102
00:05:16,367 --> 00:05:18,733
You should learn how
to give second chances

103
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:20,233
because if no one gives that,

104
00:05:20,300 --> 00:05:22,667
everyone will fight
in the world.

105
00:05:26,167 --> 00:05:27,500
Nothing is perfect.

106
00:05:28,767 --> 00:05:30,333
Everyone makes a mistake.

107
00:05:53,233 --> 00:05:54,567
Throw this in.

108
00:05:56,200 --> 00:05:57,467
- There's an ant.
- Nothing.

109
00:06:02,633 --> 00:06:04,067
I missed.

110
00:06:04,133 --> 00:06:05,367
Second chance.

111
00:06:06,967 --> 00:06:08,033
Here.

112
00:07:03,033 --> 00:07:04,367
Do you want anything...

113
00:07:04,433 --> 00:07:05,967
to eat?
I'll get it for you.

114
00:07:07,833 --> 00:07:09,333
I don't eat at night.

115
00:07:10,833 --> 00:07:12,300
You don't eat in the morning.

116
00:07:12,367 --> 00:07:13,600
You don't eat at night.

117
00:07:14,500 --> 00:07:15,933
Your life is so boring.

118
00:07:20,267 --> 00:07:21,200
Are you okay?

119
00:07:23,367 --> 00:07:25,400
I'm a bit cold.

120
00:07:33,833 --> 00:07:34,733
Come here.

121
00:07:36,533 --> 00:07:37,900
You're cold, right?

122
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:54,867
What's happening with Celeste?

123
00:08:54,967 --> 00:08:56,600
I've been trying to reach her
earlier.

124
00:08:56,667 --> 00:08:58,233
I can't seem to get through.

125
00:08:59,067 --> 00:08:59,967
Me too, Sir.

126
00:09:00,033 --> 00:09:01,300
I tried calling her
several times,

127
00:09:01,367 --> 00:09:04,000
but she's been out of range.

128
00:09:04,067 --> 00:09:07,200
Maybe her phone is turned off.

129
00:09:07,267 --> 00:09:09,000
Why would she do that?

130
00:09:09,067 --> 00:09:11,033
She knows that we call
each other every now and then.

131
00:09:12,300 --> 00:09:14,033
I don't think
she would turn off her phone.

132
00:09:14,700 --> 00:09:16,133
Maybe the battery of her phone
has no charge,

133
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:17,767
but that's impossible

134
00:09:17,833 --> 00:09:19,767
because she always has
a power bank.

135
00:09:21,200 --> 00:09:23,300
Do you have her father's number?

136
00:09:23,367 --> 00:09:25,067
Can I have it?

137
00:09:25,133 --> 00:09:28,400
I'll be restless
unless I get to talk to her.

138
00:09:28,500 --> 00:09:31,333
Can you just text me
the number, Jamaica?

139
00:09:31,400 --> 00:09:35,267
Okay, but please, don't tell
Celeste that I gave it to you.

140
00:09:35,333 --> 00:09:37,367
For sure she will get scold me.

141
00:09:37,433 --> 00:09:39,000
Sure, bye.

142
00:09:41,933 --> 00:09:45,233
Sir, you have a visitor.

143
00:09:46,767 --> 00:09:48,167
Surprise.

144
00:09:48,233 --> 00:09:49,200
Oh...

145
00:09:49,267 --> 00:09:50,433
what brings you here
so late?

146
00:09:50,500 --> 00:09:52,100
It's late into the night.

147
00:09:52,167 --> 00:09:53,533
Vivian and I had dinner.

148
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:56,833
And she asked a favor
if I could give you this.

149
00:09:58,600 --> 00:10:02,867
Okay. These are the documents
she was talking about earlier.

150
00:10:02,967 --> 00:10:05,000
Oh, is this a bad time?

151
00:10:05,067 --> 00:10:06,533
Am I disturbing you and Celeste?

152
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:07,300
No.

153
00:10:07,367 --> 00:10:09,900
She's still Sorsogon.

154
00:10:09,967 --> 00:10:11,633
Do you need anything else?

155
00:10:11,700 --> 00:10:12,733
I just want to tell you

156
00:10:12,800 --> 00:10:15,800
that I'm happy that you
and Tiffany are okay.

157
00:10:15,867 --> 00:10:18,233
I called her and she told
that me earlier.

158
00:10:21,733 --> 00:10:25,067
You know that I can't ignore
our daughter.

159
00:10:26,267 --> 00:10:29,833
You know how much I love her
and how important she is to me.

160
00:10:32,200 --> 00:10:37,367
Well, I think she's still hoping
that we will get back together.

161
00:10:37,467 --> 00:10:39,833
And we both know
that's not going to happened.

162
00:10:40,633 --> 00:10:42,800
Tiffany is having
a really hard time.

163
00:10:43,567 --> 00:10:46,000
She still can't accept it.

164
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:50,333
Well, I'm getting married
in four months.

165
00:10:50,400 --> 00:10:51,867
She needs to accept that.

166
00:10:53,300 --> 00:10:55,333
Don't be so hard on Tiffany.

167
00:10:55,400 --> 00:10:58,000
Just with me,
not to our daughter, please.

168
00:10:59,767 --> 00:11:00,967
I better go.

169
00:11:01,033 --> 00:11:02,300
- Good night.
- Good night.

170
00:11:04,167 --> 00:11:05,200
Ouch.

171
00:11:05,267 --> 00:11:06,433
Are you okay?

172
00:11:06,500 --> 00:11:07,933
I think it's the right foot.

173
00:11:08,500 --> 00:11:09,633
Come on, hold me.

174
00:11:09,700 --> 00:11:11,167
Sit down.

175
00:11:11,933 --> 00:11:13,100
Aw...

176
00:11:28,333 --> 00:11:29,533
- Here?
- Yeah.

177
00:11:44,200 --> 00:11:45,667
Aren't you going to sleep?

178
00:11:46,567 --> 00:11:48,100
Aren't you tired?

179
00:11:50,533 --> 00:11:53,167
I committed a big sin
against Celeste.

180
00:11:54,433 --> 00:11:55,900
I pushed her...

181
00:11:57,233 --> 00:11:59,333
so her heart hardened.

182
00:12:01,100 --> 00:12:04,433
The sin that I've committed

183
00:12:05,833 --> 00:12:07,533
against her and Lucinda
was really hurtful.

184
00:12:10,300 --> 00:12:13,833
It's not just you who hurt
Celeste and Lucinda, me too...

185
00:12:14,700 --> 00:12:17,133
but we both regretted
that many times.

186
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:18,967
I asked for forgiveness
several times

187
00:12:19,033 --> 00:12:20,867
in front of Lucinda's grave.

188
00:12:22,633 --> 00:12:25,767
I know I will never hear her
forgiveness

189
00:12:25,833 --> 00:12:31,667
but God knows that I'm sincere.

190
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:36,367
Could this be a punishment
for us?

191
00:12:38,500 --> 00:12:41,967
How long will that punishment
be?

192
00:12:43,467 --> 00:12:45,233
Is there no end to that?

193
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:49,633
I'm doing everything.

194
00:12:49,733 --> 00:12:52,700
I'm doing everything I know...

195
00:12:52,767 --> 00:12:55,100
just to make it up to Celeste.

196
00:12:55,167 --> 00:12:58,200
Because I want her to feel
that up to now,

197
00:12:58,267 --> 00:13:02,300
I still regret
what I did to her.

198
00:13:03,233 --> 00:13:07,167
But how long, Patricio?

199
00:13:08,367 --> 00:13:09,867
I humbly submit to her

200
00:13:09,933 --> 00:13:18,467
but do I need to kiss her feet
to forgive me?

201
00:13:19,367 --> 00:13:20,467
I don't know...

202
00:13:21,600 --> 00:13:24,767
but I will ask you one thing.

203
00:13:26,733 --> 00:13:30,267
Be more understanding
with my daughter.

204
00:13:31,400 --> 00:13:34,233
Yes, Patricio,
I'll do that...

205
00:13:34,300 --> 00:13:35,367
for you.

206
00:13:38,333 --> 00:13:39,867
But I'm just human...

207
00:13:40,967 --> 00:13:46,833
I don't know how long
I can endure your daughter.

208
00:14:30,467 --> 00:14:32,667
You're sweating, Love,
even your back.

209
00:14:33,933 --> 00:14:34,733
No problem, Love.
- That's okay.
- No.

210
00:14:35,733 --> 00:14:36,733
- Father.
- You might get sick.

211
00:14:36,800 --> 00:14:38,400
You can't get sick.

212
00:14:38,467 --> 00:14:39,467
Hey, Celeste.

213
00:14:39,533 --> 00:14:41,133
- Celeste.
- This is my classmate Mikoy.

214
00:14:41,200 --> 00:14:42,067
Good afternoon.

215
00:14:42,133 --> 00:14:44,800
- Good afternoon.
- Good afternoon.

216
00:14:44,867 --> 00:14:48,367
It looks like my daughter
has a suitor.

217
00:14:48,433 --> 00:14:49,933
Love.

218
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:51,833
No, Sir.

219
00:14:51,900 --> 00:14:55,767
Father, Mikoy and I
are just friends.

220
00:14:55,833 --> 00:14:57,733
Mikoy is a good friend.

221
00:14:58,700 --> 00:15:01,467
He carries all your stuff.

222
00:15:02,800 --> 00:15:04,867
This is a good kid...

223
00:15:04,933 --> 00:15:07,033
handsome and gentleman.

224
00:15:09,500 --> 00:15:12,333
Love, don't tease Mikoy.

225
00:15:12,400 --> 00:15:13,367
Look.

226
00:15:13,433 --> 00:15:16,533
- Oh...
- He's so pale.

227
00:15:18,733 --> 00:15:19,900
Don't get nervous, Dear...

228
00:15:20,800 --> 00:15:22,600
My point is,

229
00:15:22,667 --> 00:15:25,333
if you will court my daughter...

230
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:29,400
right now, I'm telling you,
you're approved.

231
00:15:29,467 --> 00:15:31,000
You're really something else.

232
00:15:31,067 --> 00:15:34,167
Father, that's embarrassing.

233
00:15:34,233 --> 00:15:36,400
No, that's okay, Celeste.

234
00:15:36,500 --> 00:15:39,400
Come on, I'm going to wash.

235
00:15:39,467 --> 00:15:41,600
I'll prepare our food.

236
00:15:41,667 --> 00:15:43,167
Mikoy will eat with us.

237
00:15:43,233 --> 00:15:45,200
Let's go, Celeste, come with me.

238
00:15:45,967 --> 00:15:49,167
Mikoy, forgive my husband.

239
00:15:49,233 --> 00:15:52,033
He really loves
to joke around.

240
00:15:52,100 --> 00:15:54,433
But you know...

241
00:15:54,500 --> 00:15:57,533
Celeste always tells me
about you...

242
00:15:57,600 --> 00:16:01,133
My daughter said that you
are kind,

243
00:16:01,200 --> 00:16:02,933
hardworking...

244
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:04,967
smart...

245
00:16:05,033 --> 00:16:08,267
and most of all loving
to your family.

246
00:16:09,933 --> 00:16:13,233
Just continue doing that, Mikoy.
Okay?

247
00:16:13,300 --> 00:16:18,700
A person who loves his family
will go far in life.

248
00:16:21,667 --> 00:16:22,800
Did you eat already?

249
00:16:22,867 --> 00:16:23,967
Not yet.

250
00:16:24,033 --> 00:16:25,300
Just in time.

251
00:16:25,367 --> 00:16:26,833
You should eat with us.

252
00:16:26,900 --> 00:16:29,000
I cooked a dish
in coconut milk.

253
00:16:29,067 --> 00:16:31,467
Thank you so much
but I'm not hungry.

254
00:16:31,533 --> 00:16:35,233
No, you should eat with us,
okay?

255
00:16:35,300 --> 00:16:38,767
From now on,
you should treat us your family.

256
00:16:40,667 --> 00:16:44,233
Come on, don't be shy.

257
00:16:51,233 --> 00:16:54,033
Mikoy, later I'll get
your measurement.

258
00:16:54,100 --> 00:16:57,267
I'll sew you a new polo.

259
00:16:57,333 --> 00:16:58,567
Really?

260
00:16:58,633 --> 00:17:01,367
Thank you, Ma'am.

261
00:17:01,433 --> 00:17:03,100
What's with you?

262
00:17:03,167 --> 00:17:05,000
Just call me Mother.

263
00:17:06,067 --> 00:17:11,633
You know, even if we just met,
I feel comfortable with you.

264
00:17:12,733 --> 00:17:15,600
I can feel that you
are also my son.

265
00:17:27,967 --> 00:17:29,633
Mikoy...

266
00:17:29,700 --> 00:17:31,933
even if you and Celeste
grow up...

267
00:17:33,300 --> 00:17:35,033
don't change your ways with her,
okay?

268
00:17:37,067 --> 00:17:38,633
Take care of her...

269
00:17:40,200 --> 00:17:41,767
Watch over her.

270
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:45,167
Don't leave her, please?

271
00:17:47,533 --> 00:17:50,267
I entrust my daughter to you.

272
00:17:52,967 --> 00:17:55,600
You take care of her.

273
00:17:55,667 --> 00:17:57,033
Yes, Mother.

274
00:17:57,100 --> 00:17:58,633
I will take care of her.

275
00:18:01,133 --> 00:18:03,367
Thank you so much, Son.

276
00:19:46,033 --> 00:19:47,000
How is it?

277
00:19:47,067 --> 00:19:48,767
Does it still hurt?

278
00:19:48,833 --> 00:19:50,233
A little bit...

279
00:19:50,300 --> 00:19:51,933
but it's manageable now.

280
00:19:53,700 --> 00:19:56,500
Celeste often mishaps,

281
00:19:56,567 --> 00:19:58,500
that why I'm so familiar
with it.

282
00:20:00,233 --> 00:20:01,333
Speaking of Celeste...

283
00:20:02,600 --> 00:20:05,233
what are your plans
after the wedding?

284
00:20:05,300 --> 00:20:06,367
Where will you stay?

285
00:20:07,833 --> 00:20:09,067
Well...

286
00:20:09,133 --> 00:20:11,067
I was planning to surprise her
with a dream house

287
00:20:11,133 --> 00:20:12,767
that we saw before.

288
00:20:12,833 --> 00:20:17,333
And she's planning to slow down
also with work,

289
00:20:17,400 --> 00:20:19,600
so that we could travel
and spend time together

290
00:20:19,667 --> 00:20:20,867
and build a family.

291
00:20:23,367 --> 00:20:24,500
It's really sweet.

292
00:20:26,033 --> 00:20:27,400
It makes me envious.

293
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:30,267
How I wish...

294
00:20:31,933 --> 00:20:35,167
we did that
when we were together.

295
00:20:39,967 --> 00:20:41,700
I think you're good to go.

296
00:20:41,767 --> 00:20:43,100
It's already late.

297
00:20:50,867 --> 00:20:52,333
Aurelia...

298
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:53,733
why did you do that?

299
00:20:53,800 --> 00:20:56,167
Come on, Tonito,
it's just a kiss.

300
00:20:56,233 --> 00:20:59,300
We've done more than that
when we're...

301
00:20:59,367 --> 00:21:00,433
Aurelia?

302
00:21:00,500 --> 00:21:01,567
- Tonito.
- Please leave.

303
00:21:03,233 --> 00:21:04,667
Tonito...

304
00:21:04,733 --> 00:21:06,867
don't you find this exciting?

305
00:21:06,933 --> 00:21:08,667
Celeste doesn't have to know.

306
00:21:08,767 --> 00:21:10,233
Aurelia...

307
00:21:10,300 --> 00:21:12,867
please stop this foolishness.

308
00:21:12,933 --> 00:21:15,167
Can't you understand
that we're done?

309
00:21:15,233 --> 00:21:16,567
Why are you doing this?

310
00:21:18,033 --> 00:21:21,100
Maybe it's meant to happen

311
00:21:21,167 --> 00:21:23,400
because I just got carried away.

312
00:21:24,900 --> 00:21:26,300
No...

313
00:21:26,367 --> 00:21:28,267
this is not right.

314
00:21:28,333 --> 00:21:31,167
Celeste is the woman
that I love now...

315
00:21:31,233 --> 00:21:33,133
and I will never
cheat on her.

316
00:21:35,800 --> 00:21:36,733
You know the way out.

317
00:21:38,167 --> 00:21:39,400
Tonito?

318
00:22:31,233 --> 00:22:32,233
What's with you?

319
00:22:32,300 --> 00:22:34,767
What are you doing?

320
00:22:34,833 --> 00:22:36,200
Are you a maniac?

321
00:22:37,100 --> 00:22:40,333
Oh my, maniac right away?

322
00:22:40,400 --> 00:22:42,033
I just laid you down because
my arm is hurting already.

323
00:22:42,100 --> 00:22:43,400
You fell asleep there.

324
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:48,867
Go ahead, just sleep.

325
00:22:48,967 --> 00:22:50,267
I'll watch over you.

326
00:23:10,367 --> 00:23:11,667
Close your eyes.

327
00:23:45,300 --> 00:23:48,667
Hey, fussy girl, get well.

328
00:23:48,733 --> 00:23:49,767
I want to go home.

329
00:23:51,367 --> 00:23:52,733
I'm sure...

330
00:23:52,800 --> 00:23:54,867
Tonito is already worried
about me.

331
00:23:56,767 --> 00:24:00,133
Annoying,
of all the people here,

332
00:24:00,200 --> 00:24:02,200
Mikoy is the one I'm with.

333
00:24:05,033 --> 00:24:06,367
Well, if you think about it...

334
00:24:06,900 --> 00:24:09,733
if Ms.Vangie is here with me...

335
00:24:09,800 --> 00:24:11,167
I will just be annoyed.

336
00:24:48,633 --> 00:24:50,467
Do you still remember this tree?

337
00:24:52,367 --> 00:24:54,800
No, I just passed by it.

338
00:24:56,400 --> 00:24:58,833
Impossible.

339
00:24:58,900 --> 00:25:00,967
Do you remember the day
I carved this?

340
00:25:02,867 --> 00:25:07,300
That was also the day...

341
00:25:07,367 --> 00:25:09,233
we kissed.

342
00:25:09,300 --> 00:25:12,467
Hey, are you hallucinating?

343
00:25:12,533 --> 00:25:14,133
There was no kiss that happened.

344
00:25:38,067 --> 00:25:39,200
James!

345
00:25:45,167 --> 00:25:46,600
What's the problem?

346
00:25:46,667 --> 00:25:49,133
Why did you move our meeting?

347
00:25:49,200 --> 00:25:50,833
Celeste is in trouble.

348
00:25:50,900 --> 00:25:52,133
I need to go to her.

349
00:25:52,200 --> 00:25:53,867
Your boyfriend is no longer
a war freak?

350
00:25:53,933 --> 00:25:57,467
Don't worry. I explained to him
everything about our scheme...

351
00:25:57,533 --> 00:25:59,300
and he agreed.

352
00:25:59,367 --> 00:26:00,300
I just want to make it clear

353
00:26:00,367 --> 00:26:02,167
because that fool
might get mad again.

354
00:26:03,400 --> 00:26:04,333
Who is the fool?

355
00:26:04,400 --> 00:26:05,967
It's like I feel dizzy.

356
00:26:06,033 --> 00:26:07,400
Come on, I'll carry you
on my back.

357
00:26:07,467 --> 00:26:09,367
Ouch!

358
00:26:09,467 --> 00:26:10,567
You're heavy!

359
00:26:12,000 --> 00:26:13,200
Celeste?

360
00:26:13,267 --> 00:26:14,100
Tonito...

361
00:26:17,600 --> 00:26:18,867
Why am I thinking of Mikoy?

362
00:26:18,933 --> 00:26:20,567
Can I erase, erase, erase?

363
00:26:20,633 --> 00:26:24,400
I think that fool casted
a spell on me...

364
00:26:24,467 --> 00:26:25,833
but I love Tonito.

365
00:26:26,633 --> 00:26:28,333
I can't live without him.

366
00:26:28,400 --> 00:26:29,767
Likewise, Love.

367
00:26:29,833 --> 00:26:33,867
I also can't see myself
being without you.

368
00:26:33,933 --> 00:26:36,767
Tonito, have you been there
that long?

369
00:26:36,833 --> 00:26:39,500
You heard everything I said?

370
00:26:39,567 --> 00:26:40,733
Why?

371
00:26:40,800 --> 00:26:43,767
Is there anything not true
with what you said about me?

372
00:26:43,867 --> 00:26:45,967
I'm the only Tonito
in your life, right?
